  "text": "Firefox TLS Handshake Chain: From networking layer to crypto layer. The connection flows through: (1) nsHttpConnection (netwerk/protocol/http/nsHttpConnection.cpp) - HTTP connection class that initiates HTTPS connections via nsHttpConnection::Init(). (2) TlsHandshaker (netwerk/protocol/http/TlsHandshaker.cpp) - Handles TLS setup with TlsHandshaker::SetupSSL() which gets called during connection initialization. (3) NSSSocketControl (security/manager/ssl/NSSSocketControl.cpp) - Implements nsITLSSocketControl interface that manages TLS socket control and handshake operations via NSSSocketControl::StartTLS(). (4) nsSSLIOLayerHelpers (security/manager/ssl/nsNSSIOLayer.cpp) - Bridges Necko networking to NSS crypto library by setting up NSPR I/O layers with SSL_ImportFD() at line 1274, creating PRFileDesc socket with SSL layer. (5) ssl_Do1stHandshake (security/nss/lib/ssl/sslsecur.c, line 33) - NSS internal function that orchestrates the TLS handshake state machine by calling handshake functions in a loop. (6) ssl3_HandleServerHelloPart2 (security/nss/lib/ssl/ssl3con.c) - Processes ServerHello message and continues TLS 1.3/1.2/1.1/1.0 protocol handshake with key exchange and certificate validation."
}

